			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>As a vision researcher, I find it a great problem in trying to integrate methods from cognitive sciences into computer vision as the domains they work on are so completely different. Cognitive science experiments almost always work with artificial stimuli in controlled environments such that the conclusions drawn are very rarely applicable to &#8220;real world&#8221; images, that computer vision scientists seek to solve.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

